20// Returns true iff t is an integral type where overflow is undefined
21bool no_overflow_int(Type t) {
22 return t.is_int() && t.bits() >= 32;
23}
24
25/** A mutator that moves all instances of a free variable as far left
26 * and as far outermost as possible. See the test cases at the bottom
27 * of this file.
28 *
29 * This mutator substitutes in lets. This means two things:
30 * 1) The mutate method must cache partial results
31 * 2) Users of this had better immediately run
32 * common-subexpression-elimination. Fortunately this isn't a
33 * public class, so the only user is in this file.
34 */
35class SolveExpression : public IRMutator {
36public:
37 SolveExpression(const string &v, const Scope<Expr> &es)
38 : failed(false), var(v), uses_var(false), external_scope(es) {
39 }
40
41 using IRMutator::mutate;
42
43 Expr mutate(const Expr &e) override {
44 map<Expr, CacheEntry, ExprCompare>::iterator iter = cache.find(e);
45 if (iter == cache.end()) {
46 // Not in the cache, call the base class version.
47 debug(4) << "Mutating " << e << " (" << uses_var << ")\n";
48 bool old_uses_var = uses_var;
49 uses_var = false;
50 Expr new_e = IRMutator::mutate(e);
51 CacheEntry entry = {new_e, uses_var};
52 uses_var = old_uses_var || uses_var;
53 cache[e] = entry;
54 debug(4) << "(Miss) Rewrote " << e << " -> " << new_e << " (" << uses_var << ")\n";
55 return new_e;
56 } else {
57 // Cache hit.
58 uses_var = uses_var || iter->second.uses_var;
59 debug(4) << "(Hit) Rewrote " << e << " -> " << iter->second.expr << " (" << uses_var << ")\n";
60 return iter->second.expr;
61 }
62 }
63
64 // Has the solve failed.
65 bool failed;
66
67private:
68 // The variable we're solving for.
69 string var;
70
71 // Whether or not the just-mutated expression uses the variable.
72 bool uses_var;
73
74 // A cache of mutated results. Fortunately the mutator is
75 // stateless, so we can cache everything.
76 struct CacheEntry {
77 Expr expr;
78 bool uses_var;
79 };
80 map<Expr, CacheEntry, ExprCompare> cache;
81
82 // Internal lets. Already mutated.
83 Scope<CacheEntry> scope;
84
85 // External lets.
86 const Scope<Expr> &external_scope;
87
88 // Return the negative of an expr. Does some eager simplification
89 // to avoid injecting pointless -1s.
90 Expr negate(const Expr &e) {
91 internal_assert(!e.type().is_uint()) << "Negating unsigned is not legal\n";
92 const Mul *mul = e.as<Mul>();
93 if (mul && is_const(mul->b)) {
94 return mul->a * simplify(-1 * mul->b);
95 } else {
96 return e * -1;
97 }
98 }
99
100 // The invariant here is that for all the nodes we peephole
101 // recognize in each visitor, recursively calling mutate has
102 // already moved the part that contains the variable to the left,
103 // so the right of the subexpression can be considered a
104 // constant. The mutator must preserve this property or set the
105 // flag "failed" to true.
106 using IRMutator::visit;
107
108 // Admit defeat. Isolated in a method for ease of debugging.
109 Expr fail(const Expr &e) {
110 debug(3) << "Failed to solve: " << e << "\n";
111 failed = true;
112 return Expr();
113 }
114
115 Expr visit(const Add *op) override {
116 bool old_uses_var = uses_var;
117 uses_var = false;
118 bool old_failed = failed;
119 failed = false;
120 Expr a = mutate(op->a);
121 bool a_uses_var = uses_var;
122 bool a_failed = failed;
123
124 uses_var = false;
125 failed = false;
126 Expr b = mutate(op->b);
127 bool b_uses_var = uses_var;
128 bool b_failed = failed;
129 uses_var = old_uses_var || a_uses_var || b_uses_var;
130 failed = old_failed || a_failed || b_failed;
131
132 if (b_uses_var && !a_uses_var) {
133 std::swap(a, b);
134 std::swap(a_uses_var, b_uses_var);
135 std::swap(a_failed, b_failed);
136 }
137
138 const Add *add_a = a.as<Add>();
139 const Add *add_b = b.as<Add>();
140 const Sub *sub_a = a.as<Sub>();
141 const Sub *sub_b = b.as<Sub>();
142 const Mul *mul_a = a.as<Mul>();
143 const Mul *mul_b = b.as<Mul>();
144 const Div *div_a = a.as<Div>();
145 const Div *div_b = b.as<Div>();
146
147 Expr expr;
148
149 if (a_uses_var && !b_uses_var) {
150 if (sub_a && !a_failed) {
151 // (f(x) - a) + b -> f(x) + (b - a)
152 expr = mutate(sub_a->a + (b - sub_a->b));
153 } else if (add_a && !a_failed) {
154 // (f(x) + a) + b -> f(x) + (a + b)
155 expr = mutate(add_a->a + (add_a->b + b));
156 }
157 } else if (a_uses_var && b_uses_var) {
158 if (equal(a, b)) {
159 expr = mutate(a * 2);
160 } else if (add_a && !a_failed) {
161 // (f(x) + a) + g(x) -> (f(x) + g(x)) + a
162 expr = mutate((add_a->a + b) + add_a->b);
163 } else if (add_b && !b_failed) {
164 // f(x) + (g(x) + a) -> (f(x) + g(x)) + a
165 expr = mutate((a + add_b->a) + add_b->b);
166 } else if (sub_a && !a_failed) {
167 // (f(x) - a) + g(x) -> (f(x) + g(x)) - a
168 expr = mutate((sub_a->a + b) - sub_a->b);
169 } else if (sub_b && !b_failed) {
170 // f(x) + (g(x) - a) -> (f(x) + g(x)) - a
171 expr = mutate((a + sub_b->a) - sub_b->b);
172 } else if (mul_a && mul_b && equal(mul_a->a, mul_b->a)) {
173 // f(x)*a + f(x)*b -> f(x)*(a + b)
174 expr = mutate(mul_a->a * (mul_a->b + mul_b->b));
175 } else if (mul_a && mul_b && equal(mul_a->b, mul_b->b)) {
176 // f(x)*a + g(x)*a -> (f(x) + g(x))*a;
177 expr = mutate(mul_a->a + mul_b->a) * mul_a->b;
178 } else if (mul_a && equal(mul_a->a, b)) {
179 // f(x)*a + f(x) -> f(x) * (a + 1)
180 expr = mutate(b * (mul_a->b + 1));
181 } else if (mul_b && equal(mul_b->a, a)) {
182 // f(x) + f(x)*a -> f(x) * (a + 1)
183 expr = mutate(a * (mul_b->b + 1));
184 } else if (div_a && !a_failed) {
185 // f(x)/a + g(x) -> (f(x) + g(x) * a) / b
186 expr = mutate((div_a->a + b * div_a->b) / div_a->b);
187 } else if (div_b && !b_failed) {
188 // f(x) + g(x)/b -> (f(x) * b + g(x)) / b
189 expr = mutate((a * div_b->b + div_b->a) / div_b->b);
190 } else {
191 expr = fail(a + b);
192 }
193 } else {
194 // Do some constant-folding
195 if (is_const(a) && is_const(b)) {
196 expr = simplify(a + b);
197 }
198 }
199
200 if (!expr.defined()) {
201 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
202 expr = op;
203 } else {
204 expr = a + b;
205 }
206 }
207 return expr;
208 }

210 Expr visit(const Sub *op) override {
211 bool old_uses_var = uses_var;
212 uses_var = false;
213 bool old_failed = failed;
214 failed = false;
215 Expr a = mutate(op->a);
216 bool a_uses_var = uses_var;
217 bool a_failed = failed;
218
219 uses_var = false;
220 failed = false;
221 Expr b = mutate(op->b);
222 bool b_uses_var = uses_var;
223 bool b_failed = failed;
224 uses_var = old_uses_var || a_uses_var || b_uses_var;
225 failed = old_failed || a_failed || b_failed;
226
227 const Add *add_a = a.as<Add>();
228 const Add *add_b = b.as<Add>();
229 const Sub *sub_a = a.as<Sub>();
230 const Sub *sub_b = b.as<Sub>();
231 const Mul *mul_a = a.as<Mul>();
232 const Mul *mul_b = b.as<Mul>();
233 const Div *div_a = a.as<Div>();
234
235 Expr expr;
236
237 if (a_uses_var && !b_uses_var) {
238 if (sub_a && !a_failed) {
239 // (f(x) - a) - b -> f(x) - (a + b)
240 expr = mutate(sub_a->a - (sub_a->b + b));
241 } else if (add_a && !a_failed) {
242 // (f(x) + a) - b -> f(x) + (a - b)
243 expr = mutate(add_a->a + (add_a->b - b));
244 }
245 } else if (b_uses_var && !a_uses_var) {
246 if (op->type.is_uint()) {
247 if (sub_b && b_failed) {
248 // a - (b - f(x)) -> f(x) + (a - b)
249 failed = old_failed || a_failed;
250 expr = mutate(sub_b->b + (a - sub_b->a));
251 } else {
252 // Negating unsigned is not legal
253 expr = fail(a - b);
254 }
255 } else if (sub_b && !b_failed) {
256 // a - (f(x) - b) -> -f(x) + (a + b)
257 expr = mutate(negate(sub_b->a) + (a + sub_b->b));
258 } else if (add_b && !b_failed) {
259 // a - (f(x) + b) -> -f(x) + (a - b)
260 expr = mutate(negate(add_b->a) + (a - add_b->b));
261 } else {
262 expr = mutate(negate(b) + a);
263 }
264 } else if (a_uses_var && b_uses_var) {
265 if (add_a && !a_failed) {
266 // (f(x) + a) - g(x) -> (f(x) - g(x)) + a
267 expr = mutate(add_a->a - b + add_a->b);
268 } else if (add_b && !b_failed) {
269 // f(x) - (g(x) + a) -> (f(x) - g(x)) - a
270 expr = mutate(a - add_b->a - add_b->b);
271 } else if (sub_a && !a_failed) {
272 // (f(x) - a) - g(x) -> (f(x) - g(x)) - a
273 expr = mutate(sub_a->a - b - sub_a->b);
274 } else if (sub_b && !b_failed) {
275 // f(x) - (g(x) - a) -> (f(x) - g(x)) + a
276 expr = mutate(a - sub_b->a + sub_b->b);
277 } else if (mul_a && mul_b && equal(mul_a->a, mul_b->a)) {
278 // f(x)*a - f(x)*b -> f(x)*(a - b)
279 expr = mutate(mul_a->a * (mul_a->b - mul_b->b));
280 } else if (mul_a && mul_b && equal(mul_a->b, mul_b->b)) {
281 // f(x)*a - g(x)*a -> (f(x) - g(x))*a;
282 expr = mutate((mul_a->a - mul_b->a) * mul_a->b);
283 } else if (div_a && !a_failed) {
284 // f(x)/a - g(x) -> (f(x) - g(x) * a) / b
285 expr = mutate((div_a->a - b * div_a->b) / div_a->b);
286 } else {
287 expr = fail(a - b);
288 }
289 } else {
290 // Do some constant-folding
291 if (is_const(a) && is_const(b)) {
292 expr = simplify(a - b);
293 }
294 }
295
296 if (!expr.defined()) {
297 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
298 expr = op;
299 } else {
300 expr = a - b;
301 }
302 }
303 return expr;
304 }

306 Expr visit(const Mul *op) override {
307 bool old_uses_var = uses_var;
308 uses_var = false;
309 bool old_failed = failed;
310 failed = false;
311 Expr a = mutate(op->a);
312 bool a_uses_var = uses_var;
313 bool a_failed = failed;
314
315 internal_assert(!is_const(op->a) || !a_uses_var) << op->a << ", " << uses_var << "\n";
316
317 uses_var = false;
318 failed = false;
319 Expr b = mutate(op->b);
320 bool b_uses_var = uses_var;
321 bool b_failed = failed;
322 uses_var = old_uses_var || a_uses_var || b_uses_var;
323 failed = old_failed || a_failed || b_failed;
324
325 if (b_uses_var && !a_uses_var) {
326 std::swap(a, b);
327 std::swap(a_uses_var, b_uses_var);
328 std::swap(a_failed, b_failed);
329 }
330
331 const Add *add_a = a.as<Add>();
332 const Sub *sub_a = a.as<Sub>();
333 const Mul *mul_a = a.as<Mul>();
334
335 Expr expr;
336 if (a_uses_var && !b_uses_var) {
337 if (add_a && !a_failed) {
338 // (f(x) + a) * b -> f(x) * b + a * b
339 expr = mutate(add_a->a * b + add_a->b * b);
340 } else if (sub_a && !a_failed) {
341 // (f(x) - a) * b -> f(x) * b - a * b
342 expr = mutate(sub_a->a * b - sub_a->b * b);
343 } else if (mul_a && !a_failed) {
344 // (f(x) * a) * b -> f(x) * (a * b)
345 expr = mutate(mul_a->a * (mul_a->b * b));
346 }
347 } else if (a_uses_var && b_uses_var) {
348 // It's a quadratic. We could continue but this is
349 // unlikely to ever occur. Code will be added here as
350 // these cases actually pop up.
351 expr = fail(a * b);
352 } else if (is_const(a) && is_const(b)) {
353 // Do some constant-folding
354 expr = simplify(a * b);
355 internal_assert(!uses_var && !a_uses_var && !b_uses_var);
356 }
357
358 if (!expr.defined()) {
359 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
360 expr = op;
361 } else {
362 expr = a * b;
363 }
364 }
365
366 return expr;
367 }

369 Expr visit(const Div *op) override {
370 bool old_uses_var = uses_var;
371 uses_var = false;
372 bool old_failed = failed;
373 failed = false;
374 Expr a = mutate(op->a);
375 bool a_uses_var = uses_var;
376 bool a_failed = failed;
377 internal_assert(!is_const(op->a) || !a_uses_var)
378 << op->a << ", " << uses_var << "\n";
379 uses_var = false;
380 failed = false;
381 Expr b = mutate(op->b);
382 bool b_uses_var = uses_var;
383 bool b_failed = failed;
384 uses_var = old_uses_var || a_uses_var || b_uses_var;
385 failed = old_failed || a_failed || b_failed;
386 const Add *add_a = a.as<Add>();
387 const Sub *sub_a = a.as<Sub>();
388 const Mul *mul_a = a.as<Mul>();
389 Expr expr;
390 if (a_uses_var && !b_uses_var) {
391 if (add_a && !a_failed &&
392 can_prove(add_a->a / b * b == add_a->a)) {
393 // (f(x) + a) / b -> f(x) / b + a / b
394 expr = mutate(simplify(add_a->a / b) + add_a->b / b);
395 } else if (sub_a && !a_failed &&
396 can_prove(sub_a->a / b * b == sub_a->a)) {
397 // (f(x) - a) / b -> f(x) / b - a / b
398 expr = mutate(simplify(sub_a->a / b) - sub_a->b / b);
399 } else if (mul_a && !a_failed && no_overflow_int(op->type) &&
400 can_prove(mul_a->b / b * b == mul_a->b)) {
401 // (f(x) * a) / b -> f(x) * (a / b)
402 expr = mutate(mul_a->a * (mul_a->b / b));
403 }
404 } else if (is_const(a) && is_const(b)) {
405 // Do some constant-folding
406 expr = simplify(a / b);
407 internal_assert(!uses_var && !a_uses_var && !b_uses_var);
408 }
409 if (!expr.defined()) {
410 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
411 expr = op;
412 } else {
413 expr = a / b;
414 }
415 }
416 return expr;
417 }

419 Expr visit(const Call *op) override {
420 // Ignore intrinsics that shouldn't affect the results.
421 if (Call::as_tag(op)) {
422 return mutate(op->args[0]);
423 } else {
424 return IRMutator::visit(op);
425 }

428 template<typename T, typename Other>
429 Expr visit_min_max_op(const T *op) {
430 bool old_uses_var = uses_var;
431 uses_var = false;
432 bool old_failed = failed;
433 failed = false;
434 Expr a = mutate(op->a);
435 bool a_uses_var = uses_var;
436 bool a_failed = failed;
437
438 uses_var = false;
439 failed = false;
440 Expr b = mutate(op->b);
441 bool b_uses_var = uses_var;
442 bool b_failed = failed;
443 uses_var = old_uses_var || a_uses_var || b_uses_var;
444 failed = old_failed || a_failed || b_failed;
445
446 if (b_uses_var && !a_uses_var) {
447 std::swap(a, b);
448 std::swap(a_uses_var, b_uses_var);
449 std::swap(a_failed, b_failed);
450 }
451
452 const Add *add_a = a.as<Add>();
453 const Add *add_b = b.as<Add>();
454 const Sub *sub_a = a.as<Sub>();
455 const Sub *sub_b = b.as<Sub>();
456 const Mul *mul_a = a.as<Mul>();
457 const Mul *mul_b = b.as<Mul>();
458 const T *t_a = a.as<T>();
459 const T *t_b = b.as<T>();
460
461 Expr expr;
462
463 if (a_uses_var && !b_uses_var) {
464 if (t_a && !a_failed) {
465 // op(op(f(x), a), b) -> op(f(x), op(a, b))
466 expr = mutate(T::make(t_a->a, T::make(t_a->b, b)));
467 }
468 } else if (a_uses_var && b_uses_var) {
469 if (equal(a, b)) {
470 // op(f(x), f(x)) -> f(x)
471 expr = a;
472 } else if (t_a && !a_failed) {
473 // op(op(f(x), a), g(x)) -> op(op(f(x), g(x)), a)
474 expr = mutate(T::make(T::make(t_a->a, b), t_a->b));
475 } else if (t_b && !b_failed) {
476 // op(f(x), op(g(x), a)) -> op(op(f(x), g(x)), a)
477 expr = mutate(T::make(T::make(a, t_b->a), t_b->b));
478 } else if (add_a && add_b && equal(add_a->a, add_b->a)) {
479 // op(f(x) + a, f(x) + b) -> f(x) + op(a, b)
480 expr = mutate(add_a->a + T::make(add_a->b, add_b->b));
481 } else if (add_a && add_b && equal(add_a->b, add_b->b)) {
482 // op(f(x) + a, g(x) + a) -> op(f(x), g(x)) + a;
483 expr = mutate(T::make(add_a->a, add_b->a)) + add_a->b;
484 } else if (add_a && equal(add_a->a, b)) {
485 // op(f(x) + a, f(x)) -> f(x) + op(a, 0)
486 expr = mutate(b + T::make(add_a->b, make_zero(op->type)));
487 } else if (add_b && equal(add_b->a, a)) {
488 // op(f(x), f(x) + a) -> f(x) + op(a, 0)
489 expr = mutate(a + T::make(add_b->b, make_zero(op->type)));
490 } else if (sub_a && sub_b && equal(sub_a->a, sub_b->a)) {
491 // min(f(x) - a, f(x) - b) -> f(x) - max(a, b)
492 expr = mutate(sub_a->a - Other::make(sub_a->b, sub_b->b));
493 } else if (sub_a && add_b && equal(sub_a->a, add_b->a)) {
494 // min(f(x) - a, f(x) + b) -> f(x) + min(0 - a, b)
495 expr = mutate(sub_a->a + T::make(make_zero(op->type) - sub_a->b, add_b->b));
496 } else if (add_a && sub_b && equal(add_a->a, sub_b->a)) {
497 // min(f(x) + a, f(x) - b) -> f(x) + min(a, 0 - b)
498 expr = mutate(add_a->a + T::make(add_a->b, make_zero(op->type) - sub_b->b));
499 } else if (sub_a && sub_b && equal(sub_a->b, sub_b->b)) {
500 // op(f(x) - a, g(x) - a) -> op(f(x), g(x)) - a
501 expr = mutate(T::make(sub_a->a, sub_b->a)) - sub_a->b;
502 } else if (sub_a && equal(sub_a->a, b)) {
503 // op(f(x) - a, f(x)) -> f(x) - op(a, 0)
504 expr = mutate(b - Other::make(sub_a->b, make_zero(op->type)));
505 } else if (sub_b && equal(sub_b->a, a)) {
506 // op(f(x), f(x) - a) -> f(x) - op(a, 0)
507 expr = mutate(a - Other::make(sub_b->b, make_zero(op->type)));
508 } else if (mul_a && mul_b && equal(mul_a->b, mul_b->b) && is_positive_const(mul_a->b)) {
509 // Positive a: min(f(x)*a, g(x)*a) -> min(f(x), g(x))*a
510 // max(f(x)*a, g(x)*a) -> max(f(x), g(x))*a
511 expr = mutate(T::make(mul_a->a, mul_b->a)) * mul_a->b;
512 } else if (mul_a && mul_b && equal(mul_a->b, mul_b->b) && is_negative_const(mul_a->b)) {
513 // Negative a: min(f(x)*a, g(x)*a) -> max(f(x), g(x))*a
514 expr = mutate(Other::make(mul_a->a, mul_b->a)) * mul_a->b;
515 } else {
516 expr = fail(T::make(a, b));
517 }
518 } else {
519 // Do some constant-folding
520 if (is_const(a) && is_const(b)) {
521 expr = simplify(T::make(a, b));
522 }
523 }
524
525 if (!expr.defined()) {
526 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
527 expr = op;
528 } else {
529 expr = T::make(a, b);
530 }
531 }
532 return expr;
533 }

535 Expr visit(const Min *op) override {
536 return visit_min_max_op<Min, Max>(op);
537 }
538
539 Expr visit(const Max *op) override {
540 return visit_min_max_op<Max, Min>(op);
541 }

543 template<typename T>
544 Expr visit_and_or_op(const T *op) {
545 bool old_uses_var = uses_var;
546 uses_var = false;
547 bool old_failed = failed;
548 failed = false;
549 Expr a = mutate(op->a);
550 bool a_uses_var = uses_var;
551 bool a_failed = failed;
552
553 uses_var = false;
554 failed = false;
555 Expr b = mutate(op->b);
556 bool b_uses_var = uses_var;
557 bool b_failed = failed;
558 uses_var = old_uses_var || a_uses_var || b_uses_var;
559 failed = old_failed || a_failed || b_failed;
560
561 if (b_uses_var && !a_uses_var) {
562 std::swap(a, b);
563 std::swap(a_uses_var, b_uses_var);
564 std::swap(a_failed, b_failed);
565 }
566
567 const T *t_a = a.as<T>();
568 const T *t_b = b.as<T>();
569
570 Expr expr;
571
572 if (a_uses_var && !b_uses_var) {
573 if (t_a && !a_failed) {
574 // op(op(f(x), a), b) -> op(f(x), op(a, b))
575 expr = mutate(T::make(t_a->a, T::make(t_a->b, b)));
576 }
577 } else if (a_uses_var && b_uses_var) {
578 if (equal(a, b)) {
579 // op(f(x), f(x)) -> f(x)
580 expr = a;
581 } else if (t_a && !a_failed) {
582 // op(op(f(x), a), g(x)) -> op(op(f(x), g(x)), a)
583 expr = mutate(T::make(T::make(t_a->a, b), t_a->b));
584 } else if (t_b && !b_failed) {
585 // op(f(x), op(g(x), a)) -> op(op(f(x), g(x)), a)
586 expr = mutate(T::make(T::make(a, t_b->a), t_b->b));
587 } else {
588 expr = fail(T::make(a, b));
589 }
590 } else {
591 // Do some constant-folding
592 if (is_const(a) && is_const(b)) {
593 expr = simplify(T::make(a, b));
594 }
595 }
596
597 if (!expr.defined()) {
598 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
599 expr = op;
600 } else {
601 expr = T::make(a, b);
602 }
603 }
604 return expr;
605 }
606
607 Expr visit(const Or *op) override {
608 return visit_and_or_op(op);
609 }
610
611 Expr visit(const And *op) override {
612 return visit_and_or_op(op);
613 }
614
615 template<typename Cmp, typename Opp>
616 Expr visit_cmp(const Cmp *op) {
617 bool old_uses_var = uses_var;
618 uses_var = false;
619 bool old_failed = failed;
620 failed = false;
621 Expr a = mutate(op->a);
622 bool a_uses_var = uses_var;
623 bool a_failed = failed;
624
625 uses_var = false;
626 failed = false;
627 Expr b = mutate(op->b);
628 bool b_uses_var = uses_var;
629 bool b_failed = failed;
630 uses_var = old_uses_var || a_uses_var || b_uses_var;
631 failed = old_failed || a_failed || b_failed;
632
633 if (b_uses_var && !a_uses_var) {
634 return mutate(Opp::make(b, a));
635 }
636
637 const Add *add_a = a.as<Add>();
638 const Sub *sub_a = a.as<Sub>();
639 const Mul *mul_a = a.as<Mul>();
640 const Div *div_a = a.as<Div>();
641
642 bool is_eq = Expr(op).as<EQ>() != nullptr;
643 bool is_ne = Expr(op).as<NE>() != nullptr;
644 bool is_lt = Expr(op).as<LT>() != nullptr;
645 bool is_le = Expr(op).as<LE>() != nullptr;
646 bool is_ge = Expr(op).as<GE>() != nullptr;
647 bool is_gt = Expr(op).as<GT>() != nullptr;
648
649 Expr expr;
650
651 if (a_uses_var && !b_uses_var) {
652 // We have f(x) < y. Try to unwrap f(x)
653 if (add_a && !a_failed) {
654 // f(x) + b < c -> f(x) < c - b
655 expr = mutate(Cmp::make(add_a->a, (b - add_a->b)));
656 } else if (sub_a && !a_failed) {
657 // f(x) - b < c -> f(x) < c + b
658 expr = mutate(Cmp::make(sub_a->a, (b + sub_a->b)));
659 } else if (mul_a) {
660 if (a.type().is_float()) {
661 // f(x) * b == c -> f(x) == c / b
662 if (is_eq || is_ne || is_positive_const(mul_a->b)) {
663 expr = mutate(Cmp::make(mul_a->a, (b / mul_a->b)));
664 } else if (is_negative_const(mul_a->b)) {
665 expr = mutate(Opp::make(mul_a->a, (b / mul_a->b)));
666 }
667 } else if (is_const(mul_a->b, -1)) {
668 expr = mutate(Opp::make(mul_a->a, make_zero(b.type()) - b));
669 } else if (is_negative_const(mul_a->b)) {
670 // It shouldn't have been unsigned since the is_negative_const
671 // check is true, but put an assertion anyway.
672 internal_assert(!b.type().is_uint()) << "Negating unsigned is not legal\n";
673 expr = mutate(Opp::make(mul_a->a * negate(mul_a->b), negate(b)));
674 } else {
675 // Don't use operator/ and operator % to sneak
676 // past the division-by-zero check. We'll only
677 // actually use these when mul_a->b is a positive
678 // or negative constant.
679 Expr div = Div::make(b, mul_a->b);
680 Expr rem = Mod::make(b, mul_a->b);
681 if (is_eq) {
682 // f(x) * c == b -> f(x) == b/c && b%c == 0
683 expr = mutate((mul_a->a == div) && (rem == 0));
684 } else if (is_ne) {
685 // f(x) * c != b -> f(x) != b/c || b%c != 0
686 expr = mutate((mul_a->a != div) || (rem != 0));
687 } else if (is_positive_const(mul_a->b)) {
688 if (is_le) {
689 expr = mutate(mul_a->a <= div);
690 } else if (is_lt) {
691 expr = mutate(mul_a->a <= (b - 1) / mul_a->b);
692 } else if (is_gt) {
693 expr = mutate(mul_a->a > div);
694 } else if (is_ge) {
695 expr = mutate(mul_a->a > (b - 1) / mul_a->b);
696 }
697 }
698 }
699 } else if (div_a) {
700 if (a.type().is_float()) {
701 if (is_positive_const(div_a->b)) {
702 expr = mutate(Cmp::make(div_a->a, b * div_a->b));
703 } else if (is_negative_const(div_a->b)) {
704 expr = mutate(Opp::make(div_a->a, b * div_a->b));
705 }
706 } else if (a.type().is_int() && a.type().bits() >= 32) {
707 if (is_eq || is_ne) {
708 // Can't do anything with this
709 } else if (is_negative_const(div_a->b)) {
710 // It shouldn't have been unsigned since the is_negative_const
711 // check is true, but put an assertion anyway.
712 internal_assert(!a.type().is_uint()) << "Negating unsigned is not legal\n";
713 // With Euclidean division, (a/(-b)) == -(a/b)
714 expr = mutate(Cmp::make(negate(div_a->a / negate(div_a->b)), b));
715 } else if (is_positive_const(div_a->b)) {
716 if (is_lt) {
717 // f(x) / b < c <==> f(x) < c * b
718 expr = mutate(div_a->a < b * div_a->b);
719 } else if (is_le) {
720 // f(x) / b <= c <==> f(x) < (c + 1) * b
721 expr = mutate(div_a->a < (b + 1) * div_a->b);
722 } else if (is_gt) {
723 // f(x) / b > c <==> f(x) >= (c + 1) * b
724 expr = mutate(div_a->a >= (b + 1) * div_a->b);
725 } else if (is_ge) {
726 // f(x) / b >= c <==> f(x) >= c * b
727 expr = mutate(div_a->a >= b * div_a->b);
728 }
729 }
730 }
731 }
732 } else if (a_uses_var && b_uses_var && a.type().is_int() && a.type().bits() >= 32) {
733 // Convert to f(x) - g(x) == 0 and let the subtract mutator clean up.
734 // Only safe if the type is not subject to overflow.
735 expr = mutate(Cmp::make(a - b, make_zero(a.type())));
736 }
737
738 if (!expr.defined()) {
739 if (a.same_as(op->a) && b.same_as(op->b)) {
740 expr = op;
741 } else {
742 expr = Cmp::make(a, b);
743 }
744 }
745 return expr;
746 }
747
748 Expr visit(const LT *op) override {
749 return visit_cmp<LT, GT>(op);
750 }
751
752 Expr visit(const LE *op) override {
753 return visit_cmp<LE, GE>(op);
754 }
755
756 Expr visit(const GE *op) override {
757 return visit_cmp<GE, LE>(op);
758 }
759
760 Expr visit(const GT *op) override {
761 return visit_cmp<GT, LT>(op);
762 }
763
764 Expr visit(const EQ *op) override {
765 return visit_cmp<EQ, EQ>(op);
766 }
767
768 Expr visit(const NE *op) override {
769 return visit_cmp<NE, NE>(op);
770 }
771
772 Expr visit(const Variable *op) override {
773 if (op->name == var) {
774 uses_var = true;
775 return op;
776 } else if (scope.contains(op->name)) {
777 CacheEntry e = scope.get(op->name);
778 uses_var = uses_var || e.uses_var;
779 return e.expr;
780 } else if (external_scope.contains(op->name)) {
781 Expr e = external_scope.get(op->name);
782 // Expressions in the external scope haven't been solved
783 // yet. This will either pull its solution from the cache,
784 // or solve it and then put it into the cache.
785 return mutate(e);
786 } else {
787 return op;
788 }
789 }
790
791 Expr visit(const Let *op) override {
792 bool old_uses_var = uses_var;
793 uses_var = false;
794 Expr value = mutate(op->value);
795 CacheEntry e = {value, uses_var};
796
797 uses_var = old_uses_var;
798 ScopedBinding<CacheEntry> bind(scope, op->name, e);
799 return mutate(op->body);
800 }
801};
802
803class SolveForInterval : public IRVisitor {
804 // The var we're solving for
805 const string &var;
806
807 // Whether we're trying to make the condition true or false
808 bool target = true;
809
810 // Whether we want an outer bound or an inner bound
811 bool outer;
812
813 // Track lets expressions. Initially empty.
814 Scope<Expr> scope;
815
816 // Lazily populated with solved intervals for boolean sub-expressions.
817 map<pair<string, bool>, Interval> solved_vars;
818
819 // Has this expression already been rearranged by solve_expression?
820 bool already_solved = false;
821
822 using IRVisitor::visit;
823
824 void fail() {
825 if (outer) {
826 // If we're looking for an outer bound, then return an infinite interval.
827 result = Interval::everything();
828 } else {
829 // If we're looking for an inner bound, return an empty interval
830 result = Interval::nothing();
831 }
832 }
833
834 void visit(const UIntImm *op) override {
835 internal_assert(op->type.is_bool());
836 if ((op->value && target) ||
837 (!op->value && !target)) {
838 result = Interval::everything();
839 } else if ((!op->value && target) ||
840 (op->value && !target)) {
841 result = Interval::nothing();
842 } else {
843 fail();
844 }
845 }
846
847 Interval interval_union(Interval ia, Interval ib) const {
848 if (outer) {
849 // The regular union is already conservative in the right direction
850 return Interval::make_union(ia, ib);
851 } else {
852 // If we can prove there's overlap, we can still use the regular union
853 Interval intersection = Interval::make_intersection(ia, ib);
854 if (!intersection.is_empty() &&
855 (!intersection.is_bounded() ||
856 can_prove(intersection.min <= intersection.max))) {
857 return Interval::make_union(ia, ib);
858 } else {
859 // Just take one of the two sides
860 if (ia.is_empty()) {
861 return ib;
862 } else {
863 return ia;
864 }
865 }
866 }
867 }
868
869 void visit(const And *op) override {
870 op->a.accept(this);
871 Interval ia = result;
872 op->b.accept(this);
873 Interval ib = result;
874 if (target) {
875 debug(3) << "And intersecting: " << Expr(op) << "\n"
876 << " " << ia.min << " " << ia.max << "\n"
877 << " " << ib.min << " " << ib.max << "\n";
878 result = Interval::make_intersection(ia, ib);
879 } else {
880 debug(3) << "And union:" << Expr(op) << "\n"
881 << " " << ia.min << " " << ia.max << "\n"
882 << " " << ib.min << " " << ib.max << "\n";
883 result = interval_union(ia, ib);
884 }
885 }
886
887 void visit(const Or *op) override {
888 op->a.accept(this);
889 Interval ia = result;
890 op->b.accept(this);
891 Interval ib = result;
892 if (!target) {
893 debug(3) << "Or intersecting:" << Expr(op) << "\n"
894 << " " << ia.min << " " << ia.max << "\n"
895 << " " << ib.min << " " << ib.max << "\n";
896 result = Interval::make_intersection(ia, ib);
897 } else {
898 debug(3) << "Or union:" << Expr(op) << "\n"
899 << " " << ia.min << " " << ia.max << "\n"
900 << " " << ib.min << " " << ib.max << "\n";
901 result = interval_union(ia, ib);
902 }
903 }
904
905 void visit(const Not *op) override {
906 target = !target;
907 op->a.accept(this);
908 target = !target;
909 }
910
911 void visit(const Let *op) override {
912 internal_assert(op->type.is_bool());
913 // If it's a bool, we might need to know the intervals over
914 // which it's definitely or definitely false. We'll do this
915 // lazily and populate a map. See the Variable visitor.
916 bool uses_var = expr_uses_var(op->value, var) || expr_uses_vars(op->value, scope);
917 if (uses_var) {
918 scope.push(op->name, op->value);
919 }
920 op->body.accept(this);
921 if (uses_var) {
922 scope.pop(op->name);
923 }
924 if (result.has_lower_bound() && expr_uses_var(result.min, op->name)) {
925 result.min = Let::make(op->name, op->value, result.min);
926 }
927 if (result.has_upper_bound() && expr_uses_var(result.max, op->name)) {
928 result.max = Let::make(op->name, op->value, result.max);
929 }
930 }
931
932 void visit(const Variable *op) override {
933 internal_assert(op->type.is_bool());
934 if (scope.contains(op->name)) {
935 pair<string, bool> key = {op->name, target};
936 auto it = solved_vars.find(key);
937 if (it != solved_vars.end()) {
938 result = it->second;
939 } else {
940 scope.get(op->name).accept(this);
941 solved_vars[key] = result;
942 }
943 } else {
944 fail();
945 }
946 }
947
948 void visit(const LT *lt) override {
949 // Normalize to le
950 Expr cond = lt->a <= (lt->b - 1);
951 cond.accept(this);
952 }
953
954 void visit(const GT *gt) override {
955 // Normalize to ge
956 Expr cond = gt->a >= (gt->b + 1);
957 cond.accept(this);
958 }
959
960 // The LE and GE visitors, when applied to min and max nodes,
961 // expand into larger expressions that duplicate each term. This
962 // can create combinatorially large expressions to solve. The part
963 // of each expression that depends on the variable is fixed, there
964 // are just many different right-hand-sides. If we solve the
965 // expressions once for a symbolic RHS, we can cache and reuse
966 // that solution over and over, taming the exponential beast.
967 std::map<Expr, Interval, IRDeepCompare> cache_f, cache_t;
968
969 // Solve an expression, or set result to the previously found solution.
970 void cached_solve(const Expr &cond) {
971 auto &cache = target ? cache_t : cache_f;
972 auto it = cache.find(cond);
973 if (it == cache.end()) {
974 // Cache miss
975 already_solved = false;
976 cond.accept(this);
977 already_solved = true;
978 cache[cond] = result;
979 } else {
980 // Cache hit
981 result = it->second;
982 }
983 }
984
985 void visit(const LE *le) override {
986 static string b_name = unique_name('b');
987 static string c_name = unique_name('c');
988
989 const Variable *v = le->a.as<Variable>();
990 if (!already_solved) {
991 SolverResult solved = solve_expression(le, var, scope);
992 if (!solved.fully_solved) {
993 fail();
994 } else {
995 already_solved = true;
996 solved.result.accept(this);
997 already_solved = false;
998 }
999 } else if (v && v->name == var) {
1000 if (target) {
1001 result = Interval(Interval::neg_inf(), le->b);
1002 } else {
1003 result = Interval(le->b + 1, Interval::pos_inf());
1004 }
1005 } else if (const Max *max_a = le->a.as<Max>()) {
1006 // Rewrite (max(a, b) <= c) <==> (a <= c && (b <= c || a >= b))
1007 Expr a = max_a->a, b = max_a->b, c = le->b;
1008
1009 // To avoid exponential behaviour, make b and c abstract
1010 // variables, and see if we've solved something like this
1011 // before...
1012 Expr b_var = Variable::make(b.type(), b_name);
1013 Expr c_var = Variable::make(c.type(), c_name);
1014 cached_solve((a <= c_var) && (b_var <= c_var || a >= b_var));
1015 if (result.has_lower_bound()) {
1016 result.min = graph_substitute(b_name, b, result.min);
1017 result.min = graph_substitute(c_name, c, result.min);
1018 }
1019 if (result.has_upper_bound()) {
1020 result.max = graph_substitute(b_name, b, result.max);
1021 result.max = graph_substitute(c_name, c, result.max);
1022 }
1023 } else if (const Min *min_a = le->a.as<Min>()) {
1024 // Rewrite (min(a, b) <= c) <==> (a <= c || (b <= c && a >= b))
1025 Expr a = min_a->a, b = min_a->b, c = le->b;
1026 Expr b_var = Variable::make(b.type(), b_name);
1027 Expr c_var = Variable::make(c.type(), c_name);
1028 cached_solve((a <= c_var) || (b_var <= c_var && a >= b_var));
1029 if (result.has_lower_bound()) {
1030 result.min = graph_substitute(b_name, b, result.min);
1031 result.min = graph_substitute(c_name, c, result.min);
1032 }
1033 if (result.has_upper_bound()) {
1034 result.max = graph_substitute(b_name, b, result.max);
1035 result.max = graph_substitute(c_name, c, result.max);
1036 }
1037 } else {
1038 fail();
1039 }
1040 }
1041
1042 void visit(const GE *ge) override {
1043 static string b_name = unique_name('b');
1044 static string c_name = unique_name('c');
1045
1046 const Variable *v = ge->a.as<Variable>();
1047 if (!already_solved) {
1048 SolverResult solved = solve_expression(ge, var, scope);
1049 if (!solved.fully_solved) {
1050 fail();
1051 } else {
1052 already_solved = true;
1053 solved.result.accept(this);
1054 already_solved = false;
1055 }
1056 } else if (v && v->name == var) {
1057 if (target) {
1058 result = Interval(ge->b, Interval::pos_inf());
1059 } else {
1060 result = Interval(Interval::neg_inf(), ge->b - 1);
1061 }
1062 } else if (const Max *max_a = ge->a.as<Max>()) {
1063 // Rewrite (max(a, b) >= c) <==> (a >= c || (b >= c && a <= b))
1064 // Also allow re-solving the new equations.
1065 Expr a = max_a->a, b = max_a->b, c = ge->b;
1066 Expr b_var = Variable::make(b.type(), b_name);
1067 Expr c_var = Variable::make(c.type(), c_name);
1068 cached_solve((a >= c_var) || (b_var >= c_var && a <= b_var));
1069 if (result.has_lower_bound()) {
1070 result.min = graph_substitute(b_name, b, result.min);
1071 result.min = graph_substitute(c_name, c, result.min);
1072 }
1073 if (result.has_upper_bound()) {
1074 result.max = graph_substitute(b_name, b, result.max);
1075 result.max = graph_substitute(c_name, c, result.max);
1076 }
1077 } else if (const Min *min_a = ge->a.as<Min>()) {
1078 // Rewrite (min(a, b) >= c) <==> (a >= c && (b >= c || a <= b))
1079 Expr a = min_a->a, b = min_a->b, c = ge->b;
1080 Expr b_var = Variable::make(b.type(), b_name);
1081 Expr c_var = Variable::make(c.type(), c_name);
1082 cached_solve((a >= c_var) && (b_var >= c_var || a <= b_var));
1083 if (result.has_lower_bound()) {
1084 result.min = graph_substitute(b_name, b, result.min);
1085 result.min = graph_substitute(c_name, c, result.min);
1086 }
1087 if (result.has_upper_bound()) {
1088 result.max = graph_substitute(b_name, b, result.max);
1089 result.max = graph_substitute(c_name, c, result.max);
1090 }
1091 } else {
1092 fail();
1093 }
1094 }
1095
1096 void visit(const EQ *op) override {
1097 Expr cond;
1098 if (op->a.type().is_bool()) {
1099 internal_assert(op->a.type().is_bool() == op->b.type().is_bool());
1100 // Boolean (A == B) <=> (A and B) || (~A and ~B)
1101 cond = (op->a && op->b) && (!op->a && !op->b);
1102 } else {
1103 // Normalize to le and ge
1104 cond = (op->a <= op->b) && (op->a >= op->b);
1105 }
1106 cond.accept(this);
1107 }
1108
1109 void visit(const NE *op) override {
1110 Expr cond;
1111 if (op->a.type().is_bool()) {
1112 internal_assert(op->a.type().is_bool() == op->b.type().is_bool());
1113 // Boolean (A != B) <=> (A and ~B) || (~A and B)
1114 cond = (op->a && !op->b) && (!op->a && op->b);
1115 } else {
1116 // Normalize to lt and gt
1117 cond = (op->a < op->b) || (op->a > op->b);
1118 }
1119 cond.accept(this);
1120 }
1121
1122 // Other unhandled sources of bools
1123 void visit(const Cast *op) override {
1124 fail();
1125 }
1126
1127 void visit(const Load *op) override {
1128 fail();
1129 }
1130
1131 void visit(const Call *op) override {
1132 fail();
1133 }
1134
1135public:
1136 Interval result;
1137
1138 SolveForInterval(const string &v, bool o)
1139 : var(v), outer(o) {
1140 }
1141};
1142
1143} // Anonymous namespace
1144
1145SolverResult solve_expression(const Expr &e, const std::string &variable, const Scope<Expr> &scope) {
1146 SolveExpression solver(variable, scope);
1147 Expr new_e = solver.mutate(e);
1148 // The process has expanded lets. Re-collect them.
1149 new_e = common_subexpression_elimination(new_e);
1150 debug(3) << "Solved expr for " << variable << " :\n"
1151 << " " << e << "\n"
1152 << " " << new_e << "\n";
1153 return {new_e, !solver.failed};
1154}
1155
1156Interval solve_for_inner_interval(const Expr &c, const std::string &var) {
1157 SolveForInterval s(var, false);
1158 c.accept(&s);
1159 internal_assert(s.result.min.defined() && s.result.max.defined())
1160 << "solve_for_inner_interval returned undefined Exprs: " << c << "\n";
1161 s.result.min = simplify(common_subexpression_elimination(s.result.min));
1162 s.result.max = simplify(common_subexpression_elimination(s.result.max));
1163 if (s.result.is_bounded() &&
1164 can_prove(s.result.min > s.result.max)) {
1165 return Interval::nothing();
1166 }
1167 return s.result;
1168}
1169
1170Interval solve_for_outer_interval(const Expr &c, const std::string &var) {
1171 SolveForInterval s(var, true);
1172 c.accept(&s);
1173 internal_assert(s.result.min.defined() && s.result.max.defined())
1174 << "solve_for_outer_interval returned undefined Exprs: " << c << "\n";
1175 s.result.min = simplify(common_subexpression_elimination(s.result.min));
1176 s.result.max = simplify(common_subexpression_elimination(s.result.max));
1177 if (s.result.is_bounded() &&
1178 can_prove(s.result.min > s.result.max)) {
1179 return Interval::nothing();
1180 }
1181 return s.result;
1182}
1183
1184Expr and_condition_over_domain(const Expr &e, const Scope<Interval> &varying) {
1185 internal_assert(e.type().is_bool()) << "Expr provided to and_condition_over_domain is not boolean: " << e << "\n";
1186 Interval bounds = bounds_of_expr_in_scope(e, varying);
1187 internal_assert(bounds.has_lower_bound()) << "Failed to produce bound on boolean value in and_condition_over_domain" << e << "\n";
1188 // Minimum of a boolean value is sufficient condition, implies expression.
1189 return simplify(bounds.min);
1190}

1196void check_solve(const Expr &a, const Expr &b) {
1197 SolverResult solved = solve_expression(a, "x");
1198 internal_assert(equal(solved.result, b))
1199 << "Expression: " << a << "\n"
1200 << " solved to " << solved.result << "\n"
1201 << " instead of " << b << "\n";
1202}
1203
1204void check_interval(const Expr &a, const Interval &i, bool outer) {
1205 Interval result =
1206 outer ? solve_for_outer_interval(a, "x") : solve_for_inner_interval(a, "x");
1207 result.min = simplify(result.min);
1208 result.max = simplify(result.max);
1209 internal_assert(equal(result.min, i.min) && equal(result.max, i.max))
1210 << "Expression " << a << " solved to the interval:\n"
1211 << " min: " << result.min << "\n"
1212 << " max: " << result.max << "\n"
1213 << " instead of:\n"
1214 << " min: " << i.min << "\n"
1215 << " max: " << i.max << "\n";
1216}
1217
1218void check_outer_interval(const Expr &a, const Expr &min, const Expr &max) {
1219 check_interval(a, Interval(min, max), true);
1220}
1221
1222void check_inner_interval(const Expr &a, const Expr &min, const Expr &max) {
1223 check_interval(a, Interval(min, max), false);
1224}
1225
1226void check_and_condition(const Expr &orig, const Expr &result, const Interval &i) {
1227 Scope<Interval> s;
1228 s.push("x", i);
1229 Expr cond = and_condition_over_domain(orig, s);
1230 internal_assert(equal(cond, result))
1231 << "Expression " << orig
1232 << " reduced to " << cond
1233 << " instead of " << result << "\n";
1234}

1236
1237void solve_test() {
1238 using ConciseCasts::i16;
1239
1240 Expr x = Variable::make(Int(32), "x");
1241 Expr y = Variable::make(Int(32), "y");
1242 Expr z = Variable::make(Int(32), "z");
1243
1244 // Check some simple cases
1245 check_solve(3 - 4 * x, x * (-4) + 3);
1246 check_solve(min(5, x), min(x, 5));
1247 check_solve(max(5, (5 + x) * y), max(x * y + 5 * y, 5));
1248 check_solve(5 * y + 3 * x == 2, ((x == ((2 - (5 * y)) / 3)) && (((2 - (5 * y)) % 3) == 0)));
1249 check_solve(min(min(z, x), min(x, y)), min(x, min(y, z)));
1250 check_solve(min(x + y, x + 5), x + min(y, 5));
1251
1252 // Check solver with expressions containing division
1253 check_solve(x + (x * 2) / 2, x * 2);
1254 check_solve(x + (x * 2 + y) / 2, x * 2 + (y / 2));
1255 check_solve(x + (x * 2 - y) / 2, x * 2 - (y / 2));
1256 check_solve(x + (-(x * 2) / 2), x * 0 + 0);
1257 check_solve(x + (-(x * 2 + -3)) / 2, x * 0 + 1);
1258 check_solve(x + (z - (x * 2 + -3)) / 2, x * 0 + (z - (-3)) / 2);
1259 check_solve(x + (y * 16 + (z - (x * 2 + -1))) / 2,
1260 (x * 0) + (((z - -1) + (y * 16)) / 2));
1261
1262 check_solve((x * 9 + 3) / 4 - x * 2, (x * 1 + 3) / 4);
1263 check_solve((x * 9 + 3) / 4 + x * 2, (x * 17 + 3) / 4);
1264 check_solve(x * 2 + (x * 9 + 3) / 4, (x * 17 + 3) / 4);
1265
1266 // Check the solver doesn't perform transformations that change integer overflow behavior.
1267 check_solve(i16(x + y) * i16(2) / i16(2), i16(x + y) * i16(2) / i16(2));
1268
1269 // A let statement
1270 check_solve(Let::make("z", 3 + 5 * x, y + z < 8),
1271 x <= (((8 - (3 + y)) - 1) / 5));
1272
1273 // A let statement where the variable gets used twice.
1274 check_solve(Let::make("z", 3 + 5 * x, y + (z + z) < 8),
1275 x <= (((8 - (6 + y)) - 1) / 10));
1276
1277 // Something where we expect a let in the output.
1278 {
1279 Expr e = y + 1;
1280 for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
1281 e *= (e + 1);
1282 }
1283 SolverResult solved = solve_expression(x + e < e * e, "x");
1284 internal_assert(solved.fully_solved && solved.result.as<Let>());
1285 }
1286
1287 // Solving inequalities for integers is a pain to get right with
1288 // all the rounding rules. Check we didn't make a mistake with
1289 // brute force.
1290 for (int den = -3; den <= 3; den++) {
1291 if (den == 0) {
1292 continue;
1293 }
1294 for (int num = 5; num <= 10; num++) {
1295 Expr in[] = {x * den<num, x * den <= num, x * den == num, x * den != num, x * den >= num, x * den> num,
1296 x / den<num, x / den <= num, x / den == num, x / den != num, x / den >= num, x / den> num};
1297 for (int j = 0; j < 12; j++) {
1298 SolverResult solved = solve_expression(in[j], "x");
1299 internal_assert(solved.fully_solved) << "Error: failed to solve for x in " << in[j] << "\n";
1300 Expr out = simplify(solved.result);
1301 for (int i = -10; i < 10; i++) {
1302 Expr in_val = substitute("x", i, in[j]);
1303 Expr out_val = substitute("x", i, out);
1304 in_val = simplify(in_val);
1305 out_val = simplify(out_val);
1306 internal_assert(equal(in_val, out_val))
1307 << "Error: "
1308 << in[j] << " is not equivalent to "
1309 << out << " when x == " << i << "\n";
1310 }
1311 }
1312 }
1313 }
1314
1315 // Check for combinatorial explosion
1316 Expr e = x + y;
1317 for (int i = 0; i < 20; i++) {
1318 e += (e + 1) * y;
1319 }
1320 SolverResult solved = solve_expression(e, "x");
1321 internal_assert(solved.fully_solved && solved.result.defined());
1322
1323 // Check some things that we don't expect to work.
1324
1325 // Quadratics:
1326 internal_assert(!solve_expression(x * x < 4, "x").fully_solved);
1327
1328 // Function calls, cast nodes, or multiplications by unknown sign
1329 // don't get inverted, but the bit containing x still gets moved
1330 // leftwards.
1331 check_solve(4.0f > sqrt(x), sqrt(x) < 4.0f);
1332
1333 check_solve(4 > y * x, x * y < 4);
1334
1335 // Now test solving for an interval
1336 check_inner_interval(x > 0, 1, Interval::pos_inf());
1337 check_inner_interval(x < 100, Interval::neg_inf(), 99);
1338 check_outer_interval(x > 0 && x < 100, 1, 99);
1339 check_inner_interval(x > 0 && x < 100, 1, 99);
1340
1341 Expr c = Variable::make(Bool(), "c");
1342 check_outer_interval(Let::make("y", 0, x > y && x < 100), 1, 99);
1343 check_outer_interval(Let::make("c", x > 0, c && x < 100), 1, 99);
1344
1345 check_outer_interval((x >= 10 && x <= 90) && sin(x) > 0.5f, 10, 90);
1346 check_inner_interval((x >= 10 && x <= 90) && sin(x) > 0.6f, Interval::pos_inf(), Interval::neg_inf());
1347
1348 check_inner_interval(x == 10, 10, 10);
1349 check_outer_interval(x == 10, 10, 10);
1350
1351 check_inner_interval(!(x != 10), 10, 10);
1352 check_outer_interval(!(x != 10), 10, 10);
1353
1354 check_inner_interval(3 * x + 4 < 27, Interval::neg_inf(), 7);
1355 check_outer_interval(3 * x + 4 < 27, Interval::neg_inf(), 7);
1356
1357 check_inner_interval(min(x, y) > 17, 18, y);
1358 check_outer_interval(min(x, y) > 17, 18, Interval::pos_inf());
1359
1360 check_inner_interval(x / 5 < 17, Interval::neg_inf(), 84);
1361 check_outer_interval(x / 5 < 17, Interval::neg_inf(), 84);
1362
1363 // Test anding a condition over a domain
1364 check_and_condition(x > 0, const_true(), Interval(1, y));
1365 check_and_condition(x > 0, const_true(), Interval(5, y));
1366 check_and_condition(x > 0, const_false(), Interval(-5, y));
1367 check_and_condition(x > 0 && x < 10, const_true(), Interval(1, 9));
1368 check_and_condition(x > 0 || sin(x) == 0.5f, const_true(), Interval(100, 200));
1369
1370 check_and_condition(x <= 0, const_true(), Interval(-100, 0));
1371 check_and_condition(x <= 0, const_false(), Interval(-100, 1));
1372
1373 check_and_condition(x <= 0 || y > 2, const_true(), Interval(-100, 0));
1374 check_and_condition(x > 0 || y > 2, 2 < y, Interval(-100, 0));
1375
1376 check_and_condition(x == 0, const_true(), Interval(0, 0));
1377 check_and_condition(x == 0, const_false(), Interval(-10, 10));
1378 check_and_condition(x != 0, const_false(), Interval(-10, 10));
1379 check_and_condition(x != 0, const_true(), Interval(-20, -10));
1380
1381 check_and_condition(y == 0, y == 0, Interval(-10, 10));
1382 check_and_condition(y != 0, y != 0, Interval(-10, 10));
1383 check_and_condition((x == 5) && (y != 0), const_false(), Interval(-10, 10));
1384 check_and_condition((x == 5) && (y != 3), y != 3, Interval(5, 5));
1385 check_and_condition((x != 0) && (y != 0), const_false(), Interval(-10, 10));
1386 check_and_condition((x != 0) && (y != 0), y != 0, Interval(-20, -10));
1387
1388 {
1389 // This case used to break due to signed integer overflow in
1390 // the simplifier.
1391 Expr a16 = Load::make(Int(16), "a", {x}, Buffer<>(), Parameter(), const_true(), ModulusRemainder());
1392 Expr b16 = Load::make(Int(16), "b", {x}, Buffer<>(), Parameter(), const_true(), ModulusRemainder());
1393 Expr lhs = pow(cast<int32_t>(a16), 2) + pow(cast<int32_t>(b16), 2);
1394
1395 Scope<Interval> s;
1396 s.push("x", Interval(-10, 10));
1397 Expr cond = and_condition_over_domain(lhs < 0, s);
1398 internal_assert(!is_const_one(simplify(cond)));
1399 }
1400
1401 {
1402 // This cause use to cause infinite recursion:
1403 Expr t = Variable::make(Int(32), "t");
1404 Expr test = (x <= min(max((y - min(((z * x) + t), t)), 1), 0));
1405 Interval result = solve_for_outer_interval(test, "z");
1406 }
1407
1408 {
1409 // This case caused exponential behavior
1410 Expr t = Variable::make(Int(32), "t");
1411 for (int i = 0; i < 50; i++) {
1412 t = min(t, Variable::make(Int(32), unique_name('v')));
1413 t = max(t, Variable::make(Int(32), unique_name('v')));
1414 }
1415 solve_for_outer_interval(t <= 5, "t");
1416 solve_for_inner_interval(t <= 5, "t");
1417 }
1418
1419 // Check for partial results
1420 check_solve(max(min(y, x), x), max(min(x, y), x));
1421 check_solve(min(y, x) + max(y, 2 * x), min(x, y) + max(x * 2, y));
1422 check_solve((min(x, y) + min(y, x)) * max(y, x), (min(x, y) * 2) * max(x, y));
1423 check_solve(max((min((y * x), x) + min((1 + y), x)), (y + 2 * x)),
1424 max((min((x * y), x) + min(x, (1 + y))), (x * 2 + y)));
1425
1426 {
1427 Expr x = Variable::make(UInt(32), "x");
1428 Expr y = Variable::make(UInt(32), "y");
1429 Expr z = Variable::make(UInt(32), "z");
1430 check_solve(5 - (4 - 4 * x), x * (4) + 1);
1431 check_solve(z - (y - x), x + (z - y));
1432 check_solve(z - (y - x) == 2, x == 2 - (z - y));
1433
1434 check_solve(x - (x - y), (x - x) + y);
1435
1436 // This is used to cause infinite recursion
1437 Expr expr = Add::make(z, Sub::make(x, y));
1438 SolverResult solved = solve_expression(expr, "y");
1439 }
1440
1441 // This case was incorrect due to canonicalization of the multiply
1442 // occuring after unpacking the LHS.
1443 check_solve((y - z) * x, x * (y - z));
1444
1445 // These cases were incorrectly not flipping min/max when moving
1446 // it out of the RHS of a subtract.
1447 check_solve(min(x - y, x - z), x - max(y, z));
1448 check_solve(min(x - y, x), x - max(y, 0));
1449 check_solve(min(x, x - y), x - max(y, 0));
1450 check_solve(max(x - y, x - z), x - min(y, z));
1451 check_solve(max(x - y, x), x - min(y, 0));
1452 check_solve(max(x, x - y), x - min(y, 0));
1453
1454 // Check mixed add/sub
1455 check_solve(min(x - y, x + z), x + min(0 - y, z));
1456 check_solve(max(x - y, x + z), x + max(0 - y, z));
1457 check_solve(min(x + y, x - z), x + min(y, 0 - z));
1458 check_solve(max(x + y, x - z), x + max(y, 0 - z));
1459
1460 debug(0) << "Solve test passed\n";
1461}
